# **01  Document purpose ****&**** scope**

This PRD defines what will be built, for whom, in what priority order, and to what standard. It is the handoff document from the PM layer to the engineering layer. Engineering does not begin implementation until this document is signed off.

| **Field** | **Value** |
| --- | --- |
| **Product name** | Foofoo (working name — flexible) |
| **Platform** | Android + iOS (React Native, Expo — single codebase) |
| **Primary user** | Meera — family meal planner (P0). See DOC-03. |
| **MVP goal** | 500 DAU within 90 days of launch |
| **Budget** | Under ₹25,000 total (see DOC-01 Section 09) |
| **Engineering approach** | AI-assisted development using Claude Code — no external developers |
| **Backend** | Supabase (auth, DB, Edge Functions, storage) — free tier for MVP |
| **Document version** | 1.1 — see Change Notice above for what changed from v1.0 |

# **02  The product pipeline — how Foofoo thinks**

Before features are defined, every engineer must understand this pipeline. Features are the surface. This is the engine beneath every recommendation.

| **Step 1 — Onboarding captures household signals** 5 natural questions → household_profile: main cohort, sub-cohort, home state, current city, diet type, member segments, cook capability, class preference swipes. **Step 2 — Cohort/persona assignment (silent)** household_profile → assign_persona() → persona_assignment with confidence score. 41 backend personas × 36 states. User never sees this. **Step 3 — 7-day meal CLASS plan generated** persona_assignment → generate_class_plan() → week_plan: 7 days × 3 slots × class codes. Classes are types of meals, not dishes. **Step 4 — Member add-ons attached** member_segments[] → generate_addons() → addon_slots. Infant add-on ≠ family meal replacement. Always a separate object. **Step 5 — Class → dish expansion + scoring** Hard constraints first → score via genome + regional + context + history → rank → return top 8. **Step 6 — User interaction → feedback loop** Every swipe, lock, never, rating → logged → updates class and dish-level affinity weights → next plan is more accurate. |
| --- |

| **Non-negotiable rule: the engine NEVER recommends a dish directly from cuisine preference. Class plan always comes first. Dish selection is always expansion within a class.** |
| --- |

