# **04  User stories — MVP (v1.1 — 13 stories)**

**3 user stories removed in v1.1: **US-11 (Order Instead), US-14 (Grocery list), US-16 (Referral). 13 MVP user stories remain.

## **Onboarding**

| **US-01 — As Meera:** I want to tell the app who is in my household so that it builds a meal plan for my whole family, not just me. *Acceptance: household_profile JSON matches RE-DOC-01 contract. All 5 cohort paths complete without error.* |
| --- |

| **US-02 — As Meera:** I want to tell the app my home state and current city separately so it understands both my food roots and where I live now. *Acceptance: home_state and current_city stored as separate DB fields. MP user in Pune gets MP-weighted class plan, not Pune defaults. Verified by test case.* |
| --- |

| **US-03 — As any user:** I want to skip any onboarding question without the app breaking. *Acceptance: every screen has visible Skip. Skipped diet type triggers safe omnivore default with LOW confidence. Allergens never guessed.* |
| --- |

| **US-04 — As Priya:** I want to tell the app I have an infant so I receive postpartum add-ons alongside my family's normal meals. *Acceptance: INFANT in member_segments triggers addon_slots. Add-on renders as secondary row — never as replacement.* |
| --- |

## **Home UX ****&**** plan generation**

| **US-05 — As any user:** I want to open the app each morning and immediately see today's meal plan without searching or configuring anything. *Acceptance: plan renders within 3 seconds on budget Android. Loading skeleton shown while generating. Empty state never shown without explanation.* |
| --- |

| **US-06 — As Meera:** I want to swipe through 8 alternatives for any meal slot without losing the rest of my plan. *Acceptance: carousel shows 8 ranked alternatives. Selecting updates only that slot. All other slots unchanged.* |
| --- |

| **US-07 — As Meera:** I want to lock my breakfast so it doesn't change when I refresh. *Acceptance: lock icon long-press marks slot as locked. Locked indicator visible. Pull-to-refresh skips locked slots. Lock persists across sessions until explicitly removed.* |
| --- |

| **US-08 — As any user:** I want to permanently remove a dish I hate so it never appears again. *Acceptance: long press + drag down triggers Never. Toast confirmation. Dish added to never_list. RE removes it from all future candidate sets immediately.* |
| --- |

| **US-09 — As Meera:** I want to see my infant daughter's add-on meal displayed separately so I know what to prepare alongside the main meal. *Acceptance: INFANT in member_segments: add-on row renders below relevant meal cards. Visually distinct. Only shown when member_segments is non-empty.* |
| --- |

## **Meal detail**

| **US-10 — As any user:** I want to see the ingredients I need for a dish so I know if I can cook it with what I have. *Acceptance: Meal Detail shows dish photo, name, cuisine, cook time, difficulty, simple ingredient list with rough quantities. Sourced from dish DB.* |
| --- |

## **Search ****&**** notifications**

| **US-12 — As any user:** I want to only see dishes that match my diet type — never see meals that violate my restrictions. *Acceptance: diet constraint applied as hard filter BEFORE scoring. Vegetarian user**'**s candidate set has zero non-veg dishes. SQL safety-gate returns 0 violations.* |
| --- |

| **US-13 — As any user:** I want to search for a dish by name so I can add something I'm craving even if it wasn't suggested. *Acceptance: search returns results within 500ms. Covers dish name and key attributes. Selecting result opens Meal Detail.* |
| --- |

| **US-15 — As any user:** I want a morning notification showing my breakfast so I'm reminded to open Foofoo before I start deciding what to eat. *Acceptance: notification fires at user-configured time (default 7 AM). Shows dish name, thumbnail, one-line description. Tap opens app to Day View directly.* |
| --- |

## **My Meals tab (new in v1.1)**

| **US-17 — As Meera / Arun:** I want to see what I've planned and cooked recently so I can track my meal patterns and avoid unintentional repetition. *Acceptance: My Meals tab shows dishes planned or locked, grouped by date, most recent first. Read-only in MVP. Tapping a dish opens Meal Detail. Empty state shown for new users. Minimum 30 days of history shown.* |
| --- |

# **05  Non-functional requirements**

| **Requirement** | **Specification** | **Priority** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Plan generation speed** | < 3 seconds end-to-end on budget Android (4GB RAM, Snapdragon 680 equivalent) | P0 |
| **Carousel swipe latency** | < 100ms visual response to swipe gesture | P0 |
| **Search result latency** | < 500ms from query to results rendered | P1 |
| **App cold start time** | < 2 seconds from tap to home screen | P0 |
| **API response time p95** | < 800ms for all Edge Function calls | P0 |
| **Offline capability** | Today's plan cached locally. Offline banner shown. Actions queued and synced on reconnect. | P0 |
| **Crash-free rate** | < 0.5% crash rate per session on both platforms | P0 |
| **Allergen/diet constraint integrity** | SQL safety-gate queries return 0 violations after every RE change — non-negotiable P0 release blocker | P0 |
| **Android compatibility** | Android 8.0+ (API 26+) — covers 95%+ of active Android devices in India | P0 |
| **iOS compatibility** | iOS 14.0+ — covers 95%+ of active iPhones in India | P0 |
| **Screen size support** | Works 5.0" to 6.7". No horizontal scroll on any screen. | P0 |
| **Row Level Security** | All Supabase tables have RLS enabled. Users read/write own data only. | P0 |
| **Secrets management** | Zero hardcoded secrets in committed code. All credentials in environment variables. | P0 |
| **DPDP Act 2023 compliance** | Granular consent at signup. Data export within 72h. Account deletion within 72h. | P0 |
| **Dish database minimum** | 500+ dishes fully tagged (genome, diet flags, allergen flags, class codes, photo) before launch | P0 |
| **Free tier infrastructure** | All infra runs on free tiers until 500 DAU — no paid infra before that milestone | P0 |

# **06  Feature phasing roadmap (v1.1)**

**Note: **Features F-24, F-27, F-28, F-46, F-50, F-57 are 'Phase TBD'. They will be assigned to a specific phase at the next planning session. They are not in MVP.

| **Phase** | **Timeline** | **Go/no-go criteria** | **Revenue** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **MVP — Soft launch** | Weeks 1–14 build + 90-day test | 5 of 8 MVP metrics hit. Zero constraint violations. | ₹0 — fully free. No freemium tier displayed (F-46 deferred). |
| **Phase 0.5 — Full product** | Weeks 15–20 | 500 DAU sustained 14 days | ₹0 — free period continues |
| **Phase TBD — Deferred features** | TBD | Founder to assign at next planning session | F-24, F-27, F-28, F-46, F-50, F-57 assigned here |
| **Phase 1 — Public launch** | Weeks 21–28 | D7 retention > 30%, acceptance > 40% | Ads live (if F-46 activated). Premium visible. |
| **Phase 1.5 — Monetisation** | Weeks 29–36 | 1,000 DAU, D30 retention > 25% | Premium + Ads active |
| **Phase 2 — Depth** | Weeks 37–50 | ₹1L MRR, 5,000 DAU | All streams scaling |
| **Phase 3 — Partnerships** | Year 2 | 10,000 DAU, PMF confirmed | Partnerships + all streams |

# **07  Success metrics**

***If 500 DAU is hit by Day 90 — the MVP worked. Everything else is signal, not the verdict.***

| **Metric** | **Target Day 90** | **Target Day 180** | **What failure means** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Daily Active Users (primary)** | 500 | 2,000 | Habit loop not forming |
| **Day 0 cold-start acceptance** | >25% | >35% | RE class-first pipeline failing |
| **Suggestion acceptance rate** | >40% | >50% | Genome or regional intelligence miscalibrated |
| **Day 7 retention** | >30% | >35% | No habit after first week |
| **Day 30 retention** | >20% | >28% | Product not sticky enough |
| **Onboarding completion** | >70% | >75% | Too much friction — cut a screen |
| **Never rate** | <15% | <10% | Wrong dishes for household/region |
| **App store rating** | >4.0 stars | >4.2 stars | Quality or reliability issue |

